<eventFile>special_anomaly</eventFile> 	continuity hazards, tied to fun value
<eventFile>special_boons</eventFile> 	separate event for the boon select at the start beacon
<eventFile>special_curator</eventFile> 	CURA Tasks + introduction event
<eventFile>special_defeat</eventFile> 	destruction, dead crew, escape, and surrender events
<eventFile>special_ellie</eventFile> 	Ellie's Quests
<eventFile>special_filler</eventFile> 	generic non-faction events
<eventFile>special_fleet</eventFile> 	rebel fleet events, does not contain some sector specific exit events
<eventFile>special_fuel</eventFile> 	fuel events
<eventFile>special_gb</eventFile> 		haunt and proton pack quests
<eventFile>special_guards</eventFile> 	guards + start beacons
<eventFile>special_jukebox</eventFile>
<eventFile>special_lightspeed</eventFile> 	Atlas menu
<eventFile>special_mechanical</eventFile> 	power surges and other special mechanics for player ships
<eventFile>special_morality</eventFile> 	Reputation + Notoriety
<eventFile>special_multiverse</eventFile> 	Sylvan, Leah, and Renegade encounters. Siren encounters are in events_siren
<eventFile>special_outposts</eventFile> 	outpost events that pop up in friendly sectors
<eventFile>special_piracy</eventFile> 		includes new piracy mechanics
<eventFile>special_ruins</eventFile> 		Obelisk ruins that pop up in various sectors
<eventFile>special_salvaging</eventFile> 	salvage events at empty beacons
<eventFile>special_socialize</eventFile> 	crew talking
<eventFile>special_standard</eventFile> 	stores and empty beacons, also has the Tony Sr + Butt Buddies events
<eventFile>special_storage</eventFile> 		storage checks + combat checks
<eventFile>special_transports</eventFile> 	loot transports
<eventFile>special_trapper</eventFile> 		trapper/minelayer encounters
<eventFile>special_tutorial</eventFile> 	Tutorial Only Events

<eventFile>addon_icon</eventFile> 	addons top left corner icon
<eventFile>test</eventFile> 		various testing events. These should never spawn in-game without console
<eventFile>fuel</eventFile> 		fix the fuel events


Console. Press L to use in game:

EVENT              Run an event.                           Usage: EVENT <event_id>        Example: EVENT FREE_AUG
LOADEVENT          Loads an event using LoadEvent          Usage: LOADEVENT <event_id>

LOAD               Loads a ship blueprint.                 Usage: LOAD <ship_id> <str>    Example: LOAD MANTIS_BOMBER 5 (with 5 sector strength)
ACH                Unlock achievement.                     Usage: ACH <achievement_id>    Example: ACH ACH_SECTOR_8
ACH_LOCK           Locks achievement.                      Usage: ACH_LOCK <achievement_id> Example: ACH_LOCK ACH_SECTOR_8
VICTORY            Forces a Victory and plays Credits.     Usage: VICTORY / CREDITS
SECTOR             Go to sector type.                      Usage: SECTOR <sector_type>    Example: SECTOR PIRATE_SECTOR

SCRAP              Adds/Removes scrap.                     Usage: SCRAP <num_to_add>      Example: SCRAP 500 (Negative numbers removes scrap instead)
DRONES             Adds/Removes drone parts.               Usage: DRONES <num_to_add>     Example: DRONES 50 (Negative numbers removes drone parts instead)
FUEL               Adds/Removes fuel.                      Usage: FUEL <num_to_add>       Example: FUEL 50 (Negative numbers removes fuel instead)
MISSILES           Adds/Removes missiles.                  Usage: MISSILES <num_to_add>   Example: MISSILES 50 (Negative numbers removes missiles instead)

WEAPON             Add a weapon blueprint.                 Usage: WEAPON <weapon_id>      Example: WEAPON LASER_BURST_1
DRONE              Add a drone blueprint.                  Usage: DRONE <drone_id>        Example: DRONE COMBAT_2
AUG                Add an augmentation.                    Usage: AUG <augment_name>      Example: AUG O2_MASKS
CREW               Add a crew member.                      Usage: CREW [race_name]        Example: CREW slug

SHIP_CUSTOM        Unlocks a customs ship (permanently)    Usage: SHIP_CUSTOM <ship_name> Example: SHIP_CUSTOM PLAYER_SHIP_CUSTOM
SHIP_CUSTOM_LOCK   Locks a customs ship (permanently)      Usage: SHIP_CUSTOM_LOCK <ship_name> Example: SHIP_CUSTOM_LOCK PLAYER_SHIP_CUSTOM
SHIP               Unlock a ship.                          Usage: SHIP <ship_id>          Example: SHIP PLAYER_SHIP_MANTIS
SHIP ALL           Unlock all ships                        Usage: SHIP ALL

RICH               Add 80 of each resource and 1999 scrap. Usage: RICH
POOR               Takes away all of your resources        Usage: POOR
GOD                Fully upgrade every system and reactor. Usage: GOD

DELETE             Destroys enemy ship.                    Usage: DELETE
DELETECREW         Kills everyone on the enemy ship        Usage: DELETECREW
KILL               Kills a person on your ship             Usage: KILL <crew_name>        Example: KILL John

SYS                Add a system.                           Usage: SYS <system_name>       Example: SYS cloaking
SYS ALL            Add every system.                       Usage: SYS ALL
DAMAGESYS          Damages a system                        Usage: DAMAGESYS <system_name> Example: DAMAGESYS medbay
REMOVESYS          Removes a system                        Usage: REMOVESYS <system_name> Example: REMOVESYS medbay

EXIT               Makes your location an exit beacon      Usage: EXIT
STORE              Creates a store at your location        Usage: STORE [sector]          Example: STORE 3
SKILL              Grants full skills to all of your crew  Usage: SKILL
SPEED              Changes game speed                      Usage: SPEED <speed>           Example: SPEED 3 (any integer from -2 to 3)
HULL          	   Heals/Damages your ship's hull          Usage: HULL <num_to_heal> 	  Example: HULL 10 (Negative numbers damages the hull instead)
FLEET              Advances/Delays the fleet.              Usage: FLEET <num_to_modify>   Example: FLEET 2 (Negative numbers delay the fleet instead)
SWITCH       	   Switch active ship                      Usage: SWITCH <ship_name>      Example: SWITCH PLAYER_SHIP_HARD_2
SWITCHALL          Switch active ship with equipment       Usage: SWITCHALL <ship_name>   Example: SWITCHALL PLAYER_SHIP_CIRCLE

VARIABLE           Set variable and/or print in FTL_HS.log Usage: VARIABLE <var_id> <n>
METAVARIABLE       As above but for meta-variables         Usage: METAVARIABLE <var_id> <n>
LUA                Run lua code directly for testing       Usage: LUA <code on one line>  Example: LUA print("Hello World!")
                                                                                          Example: LUA Hyperspace.Global.GetInstance():GetCApp().world.starMap:ModifyPursuit(-1)


