<FTL>
<event name="TEST_RKSHOP">
	<text>Debug Store.</text>
	<store>STORE_RADIKAL</store>
</event>
<event name="RKSHOP_SCORCH">
	<text>Debug Store.</text>
	<store>STORE_RADIKAL_SCORCH</store>
</event>
<event name="RKSHOP_SNIPER">
	<text>Debug Store.</text>
	<store>STORE_RKS_SNIPER</store>
</event>
<event name="RK_DEMI">
	<text>Debug aug.</text>
	<augment name="EX_DJMOD_DEMICLONER"/>
</event>

<event name="DJFLEET">
	<text>Fleet stopped for testing.</text>
	<modifyPursuit amount="-20"/>
</event>

<event name="RKDEV">
	<text>quick testing. Other commands: DJFLEET, TEST_RKSHOP, RKSHOP_SCORCH, RKSHOP_SNIPER, RK_DEMI, DJCOORDS, DJNOHAZARDS.</text>
	
	<weapon name="GATLING_ANCIENT"/>
	<crewMember amount="1" class="unique_billy" all_skills="2">Billy</crewMember>
	
	<item_modify>
		<item type="scrap" min="9000" max="9000"/>
		<item type="fuel" min="800" max="800"/>
		<item type="missiles" min="800" max="800"/>
		<item type="drones" min="800" max="800"/>
	</item_modify>
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>test</text>
			
			<!-- Can't give more than 1 crew per event tag. -->
			<crewMember amount="1" class="rock_commando" all_skills="2"/>
			<augment name="MULTIVERSE_DRIVE"/>
			<weapon name="LOOT_MATH_2"/>
			
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event>
					<text>test</text>
					
					<variable name="loc_internal_upgrades" op="add" val="1"/>
					<hiddenAug>UPG_AETHER_SHIELDS</hiddenAug>

					<weapon name="BOMB_STUN"/>
					<crewMember amount="1" class="engi" all_skills="2"/>
					
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>test</text>

							<variable name="loc_internal_upgrades" op="add" val="1"/>
							<hiddenAug>UPG_MEDBAY_NANO</hiddenAug>
							<variable name="loc_internal_upgrades" op="add" val="1"/>
							<hiddenAug>UPG_CLONEBAY_DNA</hiddenAug>
							<crewMember amount="1" class="phantom_goul_alpha" all_skills="2"/>
							
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="DJCOORDS">
	<text>RadiKal sector coordinates get.</text>
	<variable name="coords_radikal" op="set" val="1"/>
</event>

<event name="DJSECTOR">
	<text>opening reroute menu.</text>
	<event load="REROUTE_MENU"/>	<!-- not working. -->
</event>

<event name="DJNOHAZARDS">
	<removeHazards/>
</event>
</FTL>

<!-- 
\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
				For coordinates in stores ("Mysterious crew" operative crewjank event)
\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
 -->
<FTL>
<event name="DJMOD_OPERATIVE_DIES">
	<text>"So." Your new but already dying crew's face is dead serious. "Since you paid for me... you must be looking for... our special kind of goods, right?"</text>
	
	<!-- <choice hidden="true"> -->
	<choice req="DJMOD_NO_COORDS_NO_VISIT_RADIKAL_SECTOR" hidden="true" blue="false">
		<text>...Sure, why not?</text>
		<event>
			<text>He's clearly struggling to speak. "Then... make your way there, loaded with all the scr-... Ugh. All the scrap you can find... to fund progress. You'll find your way. M-... my mission is over." He hands you some hidden sector's coordinates, then dies.
			You notice he was already gravely injured and only held on until he could deliver this to somebody, fooling both the store owner and yourself. Some valuable tech in his pocket helps you recoup your losses. 
			
			Maybe you'll find out what that was all about the next time you reroute in hyperspeed...</text>
			<variable name="coords_radikal" op="set" val="1"/>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="scrap" min="15" max="20"/>
			</item_modify>
			
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Curious dedication, for what looks like nothing more than a black market advert.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>

	<choice req="visited_radikal_sector">
		<text>We've already visited the RadiKal sector. Rest in peace, soldier.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Progress sha- shall continue... this does bring me comfort... Thank you." He dies with a faint smile on his face.
			As usual this agent had an incurable disease and volunteered to spread awareness for RK funding and recruit reckless captains, so you're not surprised. You proceed to loot his valuable tech and dispose of the body.</text>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="scrap" min="55" max="75"/>		<!-- Net gain reward. -->
			</item_modify>
			
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>What? Of course not. Wait, are you OK?</text>
		<event>
			<text>"I... ha-... have failed." Looking mortified, he crushes a small chip inscribed with a couple capital letters, which briefly but intensely burns. Then he dies.
			
				You proceed to strip the body, notice the swelling and necrosis, and wonder why selling you illegal gear mattered more to that guy more than his impending death. You wonder if the store owner knew and just scammed you.
			At least there's some valuable tech in the dead soldier's pocket to recoup your losses.</text>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="scrap" min="25" max="35"/>
			</item_modify>
	
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>There are surely other ways to revisit this mystery and get to wherever it was going. Moving on.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
</FTL>


