</event>
<event name="RADIKAL_ENSLAVED_BADEND_MANTIS">
	<text>They bring you the slave and remove his restraints so quickly that you haven't even transferred all the scrap yet. Unfortunately the troublemaker doesn't seem to like the way some of your crew look at him, and starts punching! 
	You interrupt the scrap transfer and watch the slavers immediately jump away, leaving you to deal with him.</text>
	<item_modify>
		<item type="scrap" min="10" max="20"/>
	</item_modify>
	<instantEscape/>
	
	<boarders min="1" max="1" class="mantis_bishop"/>
	<choice>
		<text>So that's why he was so cheap.</text>
		<event load="REPUTATION_UPDATE_SLAVER"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="RADIKAL_ENSLAVED_BADEND_RK_FIREGHOST">
	<text>They bring you the slave and remove his restraints so quickly that you haven't even transferred all the scrap yet. Unfortunately the troublemaker doesn't seem to like the way some of your crew look at him, and starts punching! 
	You interrupt the scrap transfer and watch the slavers immediately jump away, leaving you to deal with him.</text>
	<item_modify>
		<item type="scrap" min="10" max="20"/>
	</item_modify>
	<instantEscape/>
	
	<boarders min="1" max="1" class="rk_fireghost"/>
	<choice>
		<text>So that's why he was so cheap.</text>
		<event load="REPUTATION_UPDATE_SLAVER"/>
	</choice>
</event>
</FTL>

<!--
		BUYERS
	Events that can remove gear and add resources.
-->
<eventList name="RK_GEAR_BUYERS">
	<event load="RK_GEAR_BUYER_ROCKMAN"/>
	<event load="RK_GEAR_BUYER_ZOLTAN"/>
</eventList>

<event name="RK_GEAR_BUYER_ROCKMAN" unique="true">
<!-- <event name="RK_GEAR_BUYER_ROCKMAN"> -->
	<preventQuest/>
	<text>You notice a Theocracy ship nearby, they immediately hail you.</text>
	<!-- <ship load="SHIP_ROCK_ESCORT_LARGE" hostile="false"/> Has a whole questline triggering mid-fight... -->
	<ship load="SHIP_ROCK_ELITE_GENERIC" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Take the hail.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Greetings, pagan. We buy RadiKal weapons, and we believe you have some."</text>
			
			<choice>
				<text>"Is that so?"</text>
				<event>
					<text>"..."</text>
					
					<choice>
						<text>"..."</text>
						<event>
							<text>"... ..."</text>
							
							<choice>
								<text>"... ... ..."</text>
								<event>
									<text>You realize they are not going to elaborate, and start considering it. What do you decide?</text>
									<!-- Sell for 150% of value, except BPS Messenger which passes all checks so 200%. -->

									<choice req="DJMOD_BAM_FISSUREBEAM" hidden="true">
										<text>Sell them your Bada beam for 155~.</text>
										<event>
											<text>You try to hide your satisfaction while they transfer the excessive payment, but also hope some unfortunate encounter won't make you regret the sale in the near future. They leave without a word.</text>
											<remove name="DJMOD_BAM_FISSUREBEAM"/>
											<item_modify>
												<item type="scrap" min="155" max="155"/>
											</item_modify>
										</event>
									</choice>

									<choice req="DJMOD_RAIN_OF_ION" hidden="true">
										<text>Sell them your Rain of Ions shotgun for 180~.</text>
										<event>
											<text>You try to hide your satisfaction while they transfer the excessive payment, but also hope some unfortunate encounter won't make you regret the sale in the near future. They leave without a word.</text>
											<remove name="DJMOD_RAIN_OF_ION"/>
											<item_modify>
												<item type="scrap" min="180" max="180"/>
											</item_modify>
										</event>
									</choice>

									<choice req="DJMOD_RAIN_OF_FIRE" hidden="true">
										<text>Sell them your Rain of Fire launcher for 120~.</text>
										<event>
											<text>You try to hide your satisfaction while they transfer the excessive payment, but also hope some unfortunate encounter won't make you regret the sale in the near future. They leave without a word.</text>
											<remove name="DJMOD_RAIN_OF_FIRE"/>
											<item_modify>
												<item type="scrap" min="120" max="120"/>
											</item_modify>
										</event>
									</choice>
									
									<choice req="DJMOD_LASER_BPS" hidden="true">
										<text>Sell them your BPS Messenger laser for 200~.</text>
										<event>
											<text>You try to hide your satisfaction while they transfer the excessive payment, but also hope some unfortunate encounter won't make you regret the sale in the near future.</text>
											<remove name="DJMOD_LASER_BPS"/>
											<item_modify>
												<item type="scrap" min="200" max="200"/>
											</item_modify>
										</event>
									</choice>
									
									<choice hidden="true" req="rock_commando">
										<text>(Commando Crew) "That kind of gear is not for brainwashed asshats. You should have stayed in your neighbourhood of stagnation and lies."</text>
										<event>
											<text>The ship's captain suddenly regains the ability for speech. "Hah! I see you work with terrorists. Once again, my brothers, witness how egotistic and violent the heretics are. Let us punish them!"</text>
											<ship hostile="true"/>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>Continue...</text>
												<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
									
									<choice>
										<text>Decline.</text>
										<event>
											<text>You think about the profit you could have made from this encounter, but also remember that selling your weapons to random passerbys isn't a very safe strategy.
												You still have time to do something around the ship instead.
											</text>

											<choice>
												<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
												<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
											</choice>
											<choice>
												<text>Do nothing.</text>
												<event/>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore them.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You don't know what they want, but do know you aren't interested in the Theocracy's deals right now.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="RK_GEAR_BUYER_ZOLTAN" unique="true">
	<preventQuest/>
	<text>Another ship, seemingly foreign, arrives at the beacon shortly after you do, looking uneasy. You could hail them and ask what's going on.</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_RK_GEAR_BUYER_ZOLTAN" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Hail them.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Hello, military ship. Um... You don't look like a RadiKal".</text> 
			<choice>
				<text>Neither do you. What does it matter?.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The ship's captain hesitates a brief moment. "You see, we are here on an... armament surveying mission you could say. And we need samples of RK gear."
					You make a mental note that this must be a secret mission, as the Ministry wouldn't normally be caught dead buying illegal weaponry.</text> 
					<choice>
						<text>Well why don't you go and get those samples?</text>
						<event>
							<text>Maybe you look trustworthy enough to that captain, because he finally spills the beans. 
							"The people in that sector don't have the best reputation and it would be regrettable for us to be seen doing business with them. We were also not really provided the right equipment to take it by force from them and then leave alive..."</text> 
							<choice>
								<text>Ask them why they're telling you this.</text>
								<event>
									<text>"Well if you have any, sell us some. Please?"</text>
									<!-- Sell for 150% of value, except BPS Messenger which passes all checks so 200%. -->

									<choice req="DJMOD_BAM_FISSUREBEAM" hidden="true">
										<text>Sell them your Bada beam for 155~.</text>
										<event>
											<text>You try to hide your satisfaction while they transfer the excessive payment, but also hope some unfortunate encounter won't make you regret the sale in the near future. They leave without a word.</text>
											<remove name="DJMOD_BAM_FISSUREBEAM"/>
											<item_modify>
												<item type="scrap" min="155" max="155"/>
											</item_modify>
										</event>
									</choice>

									<choice req="DJMOD_RAIN_OF_ION" hidden="true">
										<text>Sell them your Rain of Ions shotgun for 180~.</text>
										<event>
											<text>You try to hide your satisfaction while they transfer the excessive payment, but also hope some unfortunate encounter won't make you regret the sale in the near future. They leave without a word.</text>
											<remove name="DJMOD_RAIN_OF_ION"/>
											<item_modify>
												<item type="scrap" min="180" max="180"/>
											</item_modify>
										</event>
									</choice>

									<choice req="DJMOD_RAIN_OF_FIRE" hidden="true">
										<text>Sell them your Rain of Fire launcher for 120~.</text>
										<event>
											<text>You try to hide your satisfaction while they transfer the excessive payment, but also hope some unfortunate encounter won't make you regret the sale in the near future.</text>
											<remove name="DJMOD_RAIN_OF_FIRE"/>
											<item_modify>
												<item type="scrap" min="120" max="120"/>
											</item_modify>
										</event>
									</choice>
									
									<choice req="DJMOD_LASER_BPS" hidden="true">
										<text>Sell them your BPS Messenger laser for 200~.</text>
										<event>
											<text>You try to hide your satisfaction while they transfer the excessive payment, but also hope some unfortunate encounter won't make you regret the sale in the near future.</text>
											<remove name="DJMOD_LASER_BPS"/>
											<item_modify>
												<item type="scrap" min="200" max="200"/>
											</item_modify>
										</event>
									</choice>
									
									<choice>
										<text>Decline.</text>
										<event>
											<text>You think about the profit you could have made from this encounter, but also remember that selling your weapons to random passerbys isn't a very safe strategy.
												You still have time to do something around the ship instead.
											</text>
											
											<choice>
												<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
												<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
											</choice>
											<choice>
												<text>Do nothing.</text>
												<event/>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
							
							<choice req="DJMOD_HAS_RADIKAL_GEAR">
								<text>(RadiKal gear) Power up your weapons before they take YOUR equipment by force.</text>
								<event>
									<text>"Alright alright, no need to resort to violence. We'll be on our way."</text>
									
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>...Well that means they're as weak as they said, let's make some easy scrap!</text>
										<event>
											<text>"Wait... Wait! Thi-this was just a trade request. How did it come to this? Please!"
											As you suspected from the covert nature of their mission, they're not sending any message to denounce you, merely firing up their engines to escape! Looks like you've found a place where crime can go unpunished...</text>
											<ship hostile="true"/>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>Continue...</text>
												<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
									
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Leave them be, they are clearly no threat.</text>
										<event/>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore them.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You leave them to whatever troubles they're having, and think about doing some maintenance on your ship instead.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<ship name="SHIP_RK_GEAR_BUYER_ZOLTAN" auto_blueprint="MU_ZOLTAN_TRANSPORT">
	<!-- If you do not include a chance, then it will always attempt to surrender. -->
	<surrender chance="0.9" min="2" max="5" load="SURRENDER_ZOLTAN"/>
	<escape timer="30" min="999" max="999"/>
	<gotaway load="RK_GEAR_BUYER_ZOLTAN_GOTAWAY"/>
	<destroyed load="DESTROYED_ZOLTAN"/>
	<deadCrew load="DEAD_CREW_ZOLTAN"/>
	<weaponOverride count="1">
		<name>LIST_WEAPONS_ZOLTAN</name>
	</weaponOverride>
</ship>
<event name="RK_GEAR_BUYER_ZOLTAN_GOTAWAY">
	<text>The Zoltans escape before you can slaughter them for scrap, and contrary to what you thought, actually do denounce you. Fair enough.</text>		
	<choice>
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<!-- <event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_ZOLTAN_FIGHT"/> 	This one leads to COMBAT_CHECK -->
		<event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_ZOLTAN"/>
	</choice>
</event>


<!-- Granny on planet or "nearby station" (no sprite?) describes the 3 RadiKal subfactions if you wait. Reward for fleetboost. -->
<FTL>
<event name="RADIKAL_PHILO">
	<preventQuest/>
	<text>You find a welcoming, lively senior hermit in a small space station chock-full of civilian and military supplies, apparently all for herself. 
		"Hello foreigner, I know all about this sector, care to listen and have some tea?"</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Stay for a while. This could be helpful.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Name's Bruntilda. As you've certainly noticed, this sector is occupied by three main subfactions, and they all have their own personality!"</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Politely interrupt and ask where those supplies came from.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Oh, aren't you curious! You see my dear, my sons work in this sector in "management" and "marketing" positions. At one point they realized they didn't have the time or patience to assess newcomers and teach them our ways. So they came up with this gig for their sweet ol' mama, and they're always making sure I am cared for."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>I see. Nice to meet you.</text>
						<event>
							<text>Now that you can guess why nobody's pillaged the place yet, there are things you could learn about. "What else would you like to know, dear?"</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Think of some questions.</text>
								<event load="RADIKAL_PHILO_INTEL_LOAD"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>We don't have time to waste with some grandma's "intel".</text>
		<event>
			<text>You say goodbye, gaining and losing nothing, which isn't that bad when you think about it.</text>
			
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="RADIKAL_PHILO_INTEL_LOAD">
	<loadEvent>RADIKAL_PHILO_INTEL_REAL</loadEvent>
	
	<!-- This can help enforce randomness. probably not useful here but good reference. -->
	<!-- <loadEvent seeded="false">RADIKAL_PHILO_INTEL_REAL</loadEvent> -->
</event>
<event name="RADIKAL_PHILO_INTEL_REAL">
	<text>Ask her...</text>

	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>... about the Gatekeepers.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"This is supposed to be a bit of a surprise, but I've met some charming lads and lassies who never made it out of the sector because they didn't know. So I'll tell you: you're not leaving the sector without a fight (unless you're transporting one of our friends, hah!). Steer clear until you're prepared.
				
				The Bam gatekeeper will be a tough nut to crack, but any missile defense and sufficient shielding should keep you safe.

				The Punk gatekeeper has a bit of a chaotic mess going on, but it's mostly ion and anti-bio damage you must watch out for.

				The Scorch gatekeeper will have you on fire soon and repeatedly, and that won't work too well against it either. But surely you already figured that one out!
				
				Just don't let my sons know i told you all that, Heeeheeehee! Oh and you can always just run away if you're a pussycat..."
				You can tell that even she would no longer respect you if you did that, but you must also think about the reality you're trying to save.
				</text>
			
			<choice>
				<text>Ask her something else.</text>
				<event load="RADIKAL_PHILO_INTEL_LOAD"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Leave.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You grab your things.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Alright, we'll be on our way now. Thank you for the tea.</text>
						<event load="RADIKAL_PHILO_GOODBYE"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>... about the subfaction names.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"What kind of names are those? RadiKal Bam? Punk? Scorch? Is it from a kid's show or something?" you ask.
			
			"Not much to it really. Since so many people have been calling them radicals from the beginning of this little operation, my sons and their little friends simply embraced it. The subfactions just needed a little extra to tell themselves apart, and people don't really like talking too much around here. So they kept it short and to the point. Also I've heard something about variables? I'm the exception, chatting is so enjoyable!"
			</text>
						
			<choice>
				<text>Ask her something else.</text>
				<event load="RADIKAL_PHILO_INTEL_LOAD"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Leave.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You grab your things.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Alright, we'll be on our way now. Thank you for the tea.</text>
						<event load="RADIKAL_PHILO_GOODBYE"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>... about the RK equipment design philosophy.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Maybe you're just a little slow in the head, so just in case, let me lay it out for youuu." You repress the urge to respond to the insult.
			
			"Members of Bam believe in the blunt efficiency of impactful, stunning hits or events. Such as a good bonk to the dome, like i taught my children!
		
			The Punk prefer technological superiority, counter-intelligence and all that jazz. They tend to bring less firepower and more fancy gadgets to the table.
		
			Lastly the Scorch just want to watch things burn, and have ways to make sure they do. Some jealous foreigners like to spout nonsense about pacts with otherwordly creatures, especially among the Scorch. Isn't it sad, how low people will go?
		
			I hope that clears it up for y'all youngsters!"</text>
			
			<choice>
				<text>Ask her something else.</text>
				<event load="RADIKAL_PHILO_INTEL_LOAD"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Leave.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You grab your things.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Alright, we'll be on our way now. Thank you for the tea.</text>
						<event load="RADIKAL_PHILO_GOODBYE"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>... about the prices.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"It takes a lot of specialized equipment to discreetly get so many crafting materials into a hidden sector, or so my sons told me. That leads to high prices, but not so much for the local production of course!"</text>
			
			<choice>
				<text>Ask her something else.</text>
				<event load="RADIKAL_PHILO_INTEL_LOAD"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Leave.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You grab your things.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Alright, we'll be on our way now. Thank you for the tea.</text>
						<event load="RADIKAL_PHILO_GOODBYE"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<!-- <choice hidden="true">
		<text>... about the contests.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"The inevitable but usually friendly rivalry between the factions leads to many confrontations to figure out whose equipment is the best. 
				Even tourists like you can partake, so long as they own a piece. Sometimes they even survive!"</text>
			
			<choice>
				<text>Ask her something else.</text>
				<event load="RADIKAL_PHILO_INTEL_LOAD"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Leave.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You grab your things.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Alright, we'll be on our way now. Thank you for the tea.</text>
						<event load="RADIKAL_PHILO_GOODBYE"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice> -->
	
	<choice req="pilot" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="2">
		<text>Threaten her for the supplies!</text>
		<event>
			<text>Emboldened by her physical frailty, you decide chatting is never gonna be as useful as just taking what you want.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>How about you just shut up and give us all of those suppl-</text>
				<event>
					<text>Before you can finish your despicable threat, you feel the cold dagger belonging to a cloaked security drone pressing on your neck, and realize this whole place is obviously heavily defended.
					"Uneducated scallywags, eh? Another disappointment, but it is clear that our little business is attractive to this type of people. What a waste of good tea. Out with you now."</text>
					
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Wait a sec! You won't believe it but, this really isn't who we are...</text>
						<event>
							<text>You shamefully "offer" some supplies as an apology, find out why the pile is so big, and tell your crew in very clear terms that this event is not to be talked about ever again.
							You also feel like even though this happened in this hidden sector, word of your lack of morals could somehow reach the outside world.</text>

							<item_modify steal="true">
								<item type="scrap" min="-10" max="-20"/>
								<item type="missiles" min="-3" max="-5"/>
								<item type="drones" min="-2" max="-3"/>
							</item_modify>
							<event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_GENERAL"/>		<!-- does nothing? try in a choice wrapper -->
							<!-- <event/> -->
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<choice req="pilot" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="3">
		<text>Alright, we'll be on our way now. Thank you for the tea.</text>
		<event load="RADIKAL_PHILO_GOODBYE"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="RADIKAL_PHILO_GOODBYE">
	<text>She looks cheerful. "Why, thank you! Very few of you young'uns take a pause to listen to an old lady around these parts. For some reason they seem to favor... 'enhanced interrogation' I think the kids call it? Something about manufacturing details. Anyhoo, farewell!"
	You notice a shuttle sent to share a little of her supplies with you. That job might be lonelier than it looks, and you wonder how often her sons visit her.</text>
	<autoReward level="MED">stuff</autoReward>
	<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	
	<choice>
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>
</FTL>

<!-- QUEST SPAWNER - Anti-RadiKals police checking and fining for illegal gear, possibly seizing it, temporarily or not. 
About 900 lines, minimize if not interested. -->
<FTL>
<event name="ZOLTAN_POLICECHECK_RK">
	<preventQuest/>
	<!-- <customFleet right="false" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">CUSTOM_FLEET_ENGINEER</customFleet> 	CRASH! on sector jump -->
	<!-- <customFleet right="false" firing="false" autoDarkening="true">CUSTOM_FLEET_ZOLTAN</customFleet> 	CRASH! on sector jump -->
	<text>As soon as you get here, you notice that you're surrounded by a small Zoltan fleet intercepting every ship passing through here. An urgent hail from a heavily armed Zoltan Elite comes through. 
	Needless to say, it would look suspicious not to take the hail.
	
	[Developer note: This buggy quest will be reworked soon. Consider it a forced fight, or engage with it knowing the risks.]</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_ZOLTAN_POLICE_RK" hostile="false"/>
	<!-- <customFleet right="false" firing="false" autoDarkening="true">CUSTOM_FLEET_ZOLTAN</customFleet> 	Also CRASH below <text> -->
	<!-- <customFleet right="false" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">CUSTOM_FLEET_ENGINEER</customFleet> 	Also CRASH below <text> -->
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Answer it.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"As you may know if you're not a brainless savage, this sector has been providing armament to the Duskbringers. We have recently started tackling this problem.
			Like any vessel in transit in a lawless armament-manufacturing area like this one, you will be subjected to the mandatory thorough search for said armament. The fight against illegal weapon proliferation starts with you. Do not resist."
			Zoltans consider this area a very serious issue. If they find any RadiKal equipment, it may be confiscated, or you might be fined based on how many you're carrying.</text>
			
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Agree to the search.</text>
				<event load="ZOLTAN_POLICECHECK_RK_ACCEPT"/>
			</choice>
			
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Ask what happens if you refuse.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Thanks to the merciful recent amendment 3473-B delta, captains may choose to participate in the funding of control vessels like this one, and report to the closest Zoltan police station within 12 jump cycles instead of immediately submitting to the search."
					Even though you have no intention of taking that detour, they would leave you alone for now.</text>
					
					<!-- <choice hidden="true"> -->
					<choice>
						<text>Pay up.</text>
						<event>
							<text>You begrudgingly transfer the scrap but manage to fake a smile, taking comfort in the fact that your equipment's safe... at least for now.</text>
							<item_modify>
								<item type="scrap" min="-42" max="-42"/>
							</item_modify>
						</event>
					</choice>
					
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Agree to the search.</text>
						<event load="ZOLTAN_POLICECHECK_RK_ACCEPT"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Try to ignore it and just pass through. [Recommended]</text>
		<event>
			<text>"You admission of guilt in facilitating terrorist operations has been recorded and filed for the trial of any surviving spouse(s) and/or heir(s). You will not escape the law."
			Sounds like you'll have to fight your way through. In fact you wonder how you managed to convince yourself this could end any differently.</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<!-- <event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_ZOLTAN_FIGHT"/> -->
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
		
	<choice req="zoltan_peacekeeper" hidden="true">
		<text>(Zoltan Peacekeeper) Send the secret 'All clear' signal.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Zoltan ship immediately stops and then finds someone else to harass.</text>
			
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<ship name="SHIP_ZOLTAN_POLICE_RK" auto_blueprint="LIST_SHIPS_ZOLTAN_ELITE_GENERIC">
	<destroyed load="DEFEAT_ZOLTAN_ELITE"/>
	<deadCrew load="DEFEAT_ZOLTAN_ELITE"/>
	<!-- THIS CRASHES THE GAME upon JUMPING TO THE BEACON!
	<weaponOverride count="4">
		<name>LIST_WEAPONS_ZOLTAN</name>
	</weaponOverride> 
	-->
	<crew>
		<crewMember type="zoltan" prop="0.50"/>
		<crewMember type="zoltan_peacekeeper" prop="0.50"/>	
	</crew>
</ship>

<event name="ZOLTAN_POLICECHECK_RK_ACCEPT">
	<text>They come aboard and search your ship...</text>
	
	<choice req="DJMOD_HAS_RADIKAL_GEAR" lvl="0" max_lvl="0" hidden="true" blue="false">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>Luckily you had nothing to worry about, and after leaving your ship, without a word the Zoltans immediately cut comms to focus on a different ship. You wonder what could have happened. In any case this took a while, too long to do anything special on your ship.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<choice req="DJMOD_HAS_RADIKAL_GEAR" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="false">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>Before long, they do find something. "Understand that without justification for this, which you may still provide, we will apply the necessary sanctions, which may be a fine or outright confiscation of the offending equipment. Both may be avoided if you willingly leave someone with us for interrogation."</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="ZOLTAN_POLICECHECK_RK_OUTCOMES"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<eventList name="ZOLTAN_POLICECHECK_RK_OUTCOMES">
	<event name="ZOLTAN_POLICECHECK_RK_FINED"/>
	<!-- Seize 1 chosen RK item the player has. Keep track of which. WHY DID I DO THIS TO MYSELF"
	Leads to Police Station event below to get it back if removed, else it's just a raid with a scrap entry fee.
	Hyperspace variables to save state of things in hyperspace.xml	-->
	<event name="ZOLTAN_POLICECHECK_RK_SEIZINGS"/>
</eventList>

<event name="ZOLTAN_POLICECHECK_RK_FINED">
	<text>Maybe you forgot you were carrying RadiKal gear, or maybe you just didn't find a way to avoid the search. Regardless, they are now fining you for each piece!</text>
	<choice req="DJMOD_SUM_RADIKAL_GEAR" lvl="1" max_lvl="1" hidden="true">
		<text>Let them calculate your total fine.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"One illegal piece of gear, take this minimal fine as a warning. If you had any more "RadiKal" gear than that, we would have been forced to direct you to the local Police Station for processing."</text>
			<item_modify steal="true">
				<item type="scrap" min="-15" max="-15"/>
			</item_modify>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<!-- From here, unlocks police station quest. MAKE THIS START AT ... one piece!? -->
	<choice req="DJMOD_SUM_RADIKAL_GEAR" lvl="2" max_lvl="2" hidden="true">
		<text>Let them calculate your total fine.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Two illegal pieces of gear. You should really know better than to give up ethics for power."
			Supposedly you can get some of your scrap back by surrendering your illegal gear at the Police Station, but somehow you doubt that. It might be worth it to pay them a visit regardless.</text>
			<item_modify steal="true">
				<item type="scrap" min="-30" max="-30"/>
			</item_modify>
			
			<quest event="ZOLTAN_POLICESTATION_RK"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="DJMOD_SUM_RADIKAL_GEAR" lvl="3" max_lvl="3" hidden="true">
		<text>Let them calculate your total fine.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Three illegal pieces of gear... The federation really hires any random scum these days. We will be notifying your leadership."
			Supposedly you can get some of your scrap back by surrendering your illegal gear at the Police Station, but somehow you doubt that. It might be worth it to pay them a visit regardless.</text>
			<!-- <event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_ZOLTAN_FIGHT"/> -->
			<item_modify steal="true">
				<item type="scrap" min="-45" max="-45"/>
			</item_modify>
			
			<quest event="ZOLTAN_POLICESTATION_RK"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="DJMOD_SUM_RADIKAL_GEAR" lvl="4" hidden="true">
		<text>Let them calculate your total fine.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"FOUR or more illegal pieces of gear! What th-... I do not even wish to know. What a horrible person you must be. Luckily for you, this is the maximum fine stipulated in the applicable regulation. I suppose nobody foresaw that anyone would make themselves any more of a wretched menace to society than that."
			Supposedly you can get some of your scrap back by surrendering your illegal gear at the Police Station, but somehow you doubt that. It might be worth it to pay them a visit regardless.</text>
			<item_modify steal="true">
				<item type="scrap" min="-60" max="-60"/>
			</item_modify>
			
			<quest event="ZOLTAN_POLICESTATION_RK"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Give someone up for interrogation instead.</text>
		<event load="RK_INTERROGATED_CREW"/>
	</choice>
</event>


<eventList name="ZOLTAN_POLICECHECK_RK_SEIZINGS">
	<event name="RK_SEIZE_ONE"/>
	<!-- <event name="RK_SEIZE_SCORCHSELF2"/> etc. -->
</eventList>

