			<text>"... yes indeed. Thank you for your cooperation. Remember to pass by the Police Station to cover the post-seizure administrative fees."
			As they finally leave you alone, you wonder whether it would be possible to get your gear back.</text>
			<quest event="ZOLTAN_POLICESTATION_RK"/>
			
			<variable name="seized_laserbps" op="add" val="1"/>
			<remove name="DJMOD_LASER_BPS"/>
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<!-- Equipment choices end -->
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Headshot that nosy lightbulb. (Risky)</text>
		<event>
			<text>Quickly but accurately aiming through the hardlight, you splatter the chief inspector with your blaster, right before taking cover for the explosion! 
			Very satisfying ... but can you deal with the rest of them?</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<boarders min="5" max="7" class="zoltan_peacekeeper"/>
			
			<choice>
				<text>Pop them all!</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<!-- <choice req="DJMOD_ANY_CREW" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="true">  -->
	<choice req="LIST_CHECK_ANY_CREW" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="true">
		<text>Give someone up for interrogation instead.</text>
		<event load="RK_INTERROGATED_CREW"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="RK_INTERROGATED_CREW">
	<text>You come to an agreement where they keep one of your crew in custody so they can explain what you were doing in this sector. It's a lengthy process, you will certainly finish your mission (or die) before you see them again.</text>
	<removeCrew>			<!--No class argument means it's a random crewmember.-->
		<clone>false</clone>
		<text>Your crew cannot be cloned as they are not dead, though they might go insane shortly.</text>
	</removeCrew>
	
	<choice>
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>

</FTL>

<!-- Safeguards RadiKal gear confiscated by Zoltan Police in event above. Player can raid to get gear back or just loot. -->
<!-- <event name="ZOLTAN_POLICESTATION_RK" unique="true"> -->
<event name="ZOLTAN_POLICESTATION_RK">
	<preventQuest/>
	<preventFleet/>
	<quest>
		<nebulaBeacon>false</nebulaBeacon>
		<aggressive>2</aggressive>			<!-- what does that even do? -->
	</quest>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_rk_policestation" global="true">
		<color r="94" g="255" b="94" a="1.0"/>
		<unvisitedTooltip>Where Zoltan Police holds confiscated RadiKal gear and seized supplies.</unvisitedTooltip>
	</beaconType>
	<text>You wonder how exactly the Zoltans set up a fortified police station in such an area undeterred, but it is proof of their determination.
	"Welcome captain. Since you found this place, you must be part of the special Federation corps attached to this regulation effort." Might be far from the truth, but you decide to roll with it.
	"What can we do for you?"</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_ZOLTAN_POLICESTATION_RK" hostile="false"/>
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Request supplies.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"We have seized quite a lot of supplies from this band of criminals, at great cost. But you are our ally in this operation, so help yourself. Within the limits of the Alliance Supply and Logistics Act of course."</text>
			<autoReward level="MED">stuff</autoReward>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Request RadiKal gear.</text>
		<event>
			<text>After some brief icebreaker chitchat which the officer seems to midly enjoy, you take your shot asking for a free piece. What passes for his facial expression changes that instant. 
				"Surely you must be confused. This is labeled and sorted trial evidence, in the form of illegal weaponry which is unsafe for use, unethical and generally a threat to law and order. Thanks for stopping by, I have work to do now."</text>
			
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Feign surprise.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You expected this. "Oh? We weren't informed. Sorry for asking, keep up the good work." 
						The Zoltan throws you one suspicious look, but he's too busy dealing with the paperwork to investigate, and you're out without a hitch, but with nothing to show for it.</text>
					<event/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Hint that you can do this the hard way instead...</text>
				<event>
					<text>Now certain that you're not, in fact, here to help at all, the Zoltan rings the alarm and you rush back to your ship. The fight is breaking out within range of the station's defense turrets!</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
					<environment type="PDS" target="player"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<choice req="DJMOD_WAS_SEIZED_RADIKAL_GEAR" hidden="true">
		<text>(Seized equipment) Inquire about your gear. (Risky)</text>
		<event>
			<text>Confused, the officer briefly searches for it in the database. "Hold on... the ship this piece was found on is YOURS! You must be here to steal it back! I will no-"
			Before he can finish, you permanently silence him with a blaster shot to the face, find and grab your equipment thanks to the info he just brought up, then get the hell out before the defense turrets can land more than a couple hits on your hull.
			Your rap sheet is getting longer by the minute!</text>
			<damage amount="2" system="room"/>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<environment type="PDS" target="player"/>
			
			<choice req="seized_shipvoreram" hidden="true">
				<text>Put the gear back on your ship.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You are delighted to have it back. Your crew has mixed feelings, but you remind them of the mission.</text>
					<augment name="DJMOD_COMBAT_SHIPVORE_RAM"/>
					<variable name="seized_shipvoreram" op="add" val="-1"/>
					
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_ZOLTAN_FIGHT"/>
