<ship name="SHIP_ZOLTAN_POLICESTATION_RK" auto_blueprint="MU_ZOLTAN_STATION">
	<destroyed>
		<text>The police station breaks apart, its confiscated illegal contents and extensive array of administrative backups reduced to mere scrap for you to take.</text>
		<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
	</destroyed>
	<deadCrew>
		<text>Having killed the crew, you manage to snatch some supplies and a labeled crate before the turrets tear your ship apart.</text>
		<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Open it.</text>
			<event>
				<text>As the label suggested, it's a RadiKal augment! Bureaucracy has its benefits.</text>
				<augment name="GIFTLIST_AUGMENT_RADIKAL"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
	</deadCrew>
	<crew>
		<crewMember type="zoltan" prop="0.50"/>
		<crewMember type="zoltan_peacekeeper" prop="0.50"/>	
	</crew>
</ship>


<!-- 
RK ships under attack, giving subfaction-theme-fitting gear when saved, or RK gear when crewkilled. 
_LASERS version updated 5.5.1, re-copypaste the others completely, based on this one.
-->
<FTL>
<event name="THIEVES_RK_LASERS">
	<text>It appears a damaged laser-wielding RadiKal ship is under attack by an Argeonn smuggler, certainly to steal their special tech. They are on their last legs but their trajectory forces them to pass you by for a slim chance at escaping.</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_SMUGGLER_RK_LASERS" hostile="false"/>
	
	<choice>
		<text>Rescue the RadiKals.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You give the smuggler ship no choice but to fight you as you take position in their way.</text> 
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<choice hidden="true" req="weapons" lvl="5">
		<text>(Upg. Weapons) Claim the prey for yourself.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Woh hoh hoh, hey, wait, that's our-" They quickly change their mind as the rest of the crew pressures them. "You know what, screw this, have fun with you ill-gotten goods." Quite ironic, coming from a smuggler. The surviving RadiKals are easily dealt with.</text>
			<autoReward level="LOW">standard</autoReward>
			
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Search the ship a little more.</text>
				<event>
					<text>There was a functional RadiKal augment in the cargo! Must be what the smugglers were after.</text>
					<augment name="GIFTLIST_AUGMENT_RADIKAL"/>

					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>I guess we're the thieves now.</text>
						
						<event load="REPUTATION_DECREASE_SMUGGLING"/>
						<!-- <event load="REPUTATION_UPDATE_SMUGGLING_FREE"/> -->
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>

	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Stay back and watch how this unfolds.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The RadiKal ship puts up a decent but hopeless fight and soon stops showing signs of life. The pirates briefly do whatever they went in there for, then re-open comms with you. "Thank you for not interfering my good sir. Imagine how much easier business would be if we had more cowa- i mean nice bystanders like you around? Here's some fuel for your exemplary behavior, and we're off to celebrate!" You scoop up the reward and briefly wonder what could have put them in such a good mood.</text>
			<autoReward level="LOW">fuel_only</autoReward>
			<!-- <item_modify>
				<item type="scrap" min="5" max="10"/>
			</item_modify> -->
			<instantEscape/>
			
			<choice>
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="REPUTATION_UPDATE_SMUGGLING_FREE"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore them.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You leave the ships to their fight and think about what to do next.</text>
			
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<!-- TODO: TEST: if no work, move to events_ships & RETEST. -->
<ship name="SHIP_SMUGGLER_RK_LASERS" auto_blueprint="LIST_SHIPS_SMUGGLERS">
	<!-- <surrender min="999" max="999" load="SURRENDER_PIRATE"/> this is an instant surrender, which can be used for any event actually, like Guard ASB call. -->
	<!-- <surrender min="1" max="2" load="CRYSTAL_BOSS_SURRENDER"/> REF from spare crystal queen unlock quest. -->
	<!-- <surrender chance="0.4" min="2" max="3" load="THIEVES_RK_LASERS_REWARD_SURR"/> IT NEVER CONTINUES THE QUESTLINE, JUST GIVES SURR REWARD -->
	<!-- <surrender min="1" max="3" load="SHIP_SMUGGLER_RK_LASERS_SURRENDER"/> This name format doesn't work either. -->
	
	<destroyed load="THIEVES_RK_LASERS_REWARD"/>
	<deadCrew load="THIEVES_RK_LASERS_REWARD_CREWKILL"/>
</ship>

<event name="SHIP_SMUGGLER_RK_LASERS_SURRENDER">
	<text load="TEXT_SURRENDER_PIRATE"/>
	<choice>
		<text>Accept their surrender.</text>
		<event>
			<ship hostile="false"/>
			<autoReward level="LOW">stuff</autoReward>
			
			<choice>
				<text>Go and check on their would-be prey.</text>
				<event load="THIEVES_RK_LASERS_REWARD"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text load="GENERIC_SURRENDER_CHOICE_NOMERCY"/>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="THIEVES_RK_LASERS_REWARD">
	<text>"Without you we were toast. Have this as thanks."</text>
	<autoReward level="LOW">standard</autoReward>
	
	<choice>
		<text>What did they want from you?</text>
		<event load="THIEVES_RK_LASERS_END"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="THIEVES_RK_LASERS_REWARD_CREWKILL">
	<text>"Without you we were toast. Have this as thanks."</text>
	<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
	
	<choice>
		<text>What did they want from you?</text>
		<event load="THIEVES_RK_LASERS_END"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="THIEVES_RK_LASERS_END">
	<text>"The usual, local tech. Surely you understand that we can't just give it to you either. However we can provide you one laser weapon from our cargo that fits your preferred RadiKal subfaction, that would only be fair. Which one is it?"</text> 
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Bam!</text>
		<event>
			<text>They transfer the weapon and wish you safe travels.</text> 
			<weapon name="GIFTLIST_FITTING_LASER_BAM"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Punk!</text>
		<event>
			<text>They transfer the weapon and wish you safe travels.</text> 
			<weapon name="GIFTLIST_FITTING_LASER_PUNK"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Scorch!</text>
		<event>
			<text>They transfer the weapon and wish you safe travels.</text> 
			<weapon name="GIFTLIST_FITTING_LASER_SCORCH"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

</FTL>

<FTL>
<event name="THIEVES_RK_MISSILES">
	<text>It appears a damaged missile-wielding RadiKal ship is under attack by a smuggler, certainly to steal their special tech. They are on their last legs but their trajectory forces them to pass you by for a slim chance at escaping.</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_SMUGGLER_RK_MISSILES" hostile="false"/>
	
	<choice>
		<text>Rescue the RadiKals.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You give the smuggler ship no choice but to fight you as you fly towards it full speed.</text> 
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
