<!-- Empty beacons -->
<FTL>
<event name="EMPTY_RADIKAL">
	<text load="EMPTY_RADIKAL"/>
	<choice>
		<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
		<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Do nothing.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>
<textList name="EMPTY_RADIKAL">
	<text>You arrive at the beacon and are relieved to get a break, as nobody here seems to care about what tech you do or don't have.</text>
	<text>No other ships or interesting structures can be found here, a chance to do some work on your ship, or chat with your crew maybe.</text>
	<text>This sector isn't exactly what you'd call calm, but here at least there is nothing going on worthy of attention.</text>
	<text>Looks like you've found a relatively peaceful spot, a rarity in this sector.</text>
	<text>A weapons test seems to have gone catastrophically wrong around here recently, and the place is currently abandoned.</text>
</textList>
<event name="NEBULA_EMPTY_RADIKAL">
	<environment type="nebula"/>
	<text load="NEBULA_EMPTY_RADIKAL"/>
	<choice>
		<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
		<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Do nothing.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>
<textList name="NEBULA_EMPTY_RADIKAL">
	<text>It looks like this nebula is a good hiding spot for now, no hostiles detected.</text>
	<text>You won't find any special tech here, but nobody to bother you either, not even ambushing pirates.</text>
	<text>This beacon is closed off for security reasons, but that's all the computer says. You can probably enjoy the mesmerizing nebula without getting hit by some experimental weapon.</text>
</textList>
</FTL>

