<!-- Crash WAS from here. All events of the chain were crashless when consoled, so _LOADER technique once again fixed.
Except this time the loader is EXIT_RADIKAL so i'm not changing the name for consistency with other sectors. -->
<event name="EXIT_RADIKAL">
	<loadEvent seeded="false">EXIT_RADIKAL_PART2</loadEvent>
</event>
<!-- Copy-paste of the above -->
 <event name="NEBULA_EXIT_RADIKAL">
	<loadEvent seeded="false">EXIT_RADIKAL_PART2</loadEvent>
</event>


<event name="EXIT_RADIKAL_PART2">
	<text>You're arrived at the exit alive, which is no small feat, but three menacing ships have been waiting for you.
		Accurately guessing that you don't have a choice, you answer the hail.</text>
	
	<!-- <ship load="SHIP_RADIKAL_EXIT_BOSS" hostile="false"/> Don't load yet, but now we CAN fight 2+ ships per beacon. -->
	<choice req="RKS_TRYING_TO_SKIP_TRINITY" lvl="0" max_lvl="0" hidden="true" blue="false">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="EXIT_RADIKAL_MAIN"/>
	</choice>
	<choice req="RKS_TRYING_TO_SKIP_TRINITY" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="false">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="EXIT_RADIKAL_ACTIVATE_PIRATE_AMBUSH"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="EXIT_RADIKAL_ACTIVATE_PIRATE_AMBUSH">
	<text>You have this weird feeling like you've forgotten to do something important... but you carry on.</text>
	<jumpEvent>RKS_EXIT_PIRATE_TRINITY_AMBUSH</jumpEvent>
	
	<choice>
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="EXIT_RADIKAL_MAIN"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="EXIT_RADIKAL_MAIN">
	<text>"I'll make it simple for you, we have a reputation to uphold. If you're not able to beat one of our gatekeepers, we can't let you leave and make RadiKal gear look bad with your incompetence.
	Think about it. Why do you think folks fund all of this? That's because you've never heard of subpar RadiKal equipment, and this is one way to do quality control.
	You do get to pick your opponent, so choose wisely... yeah, that IS part of the skill test.
	Oh and, don't worry about killing crew in these ships, they're all purpose-grown illegal clones. In fact we'd like to see you try to kill them cleanly."
	</text>
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Fight the Bam Gatekeeper!</text>
		<event>
			<text>You think your best shot is against the Bam, with their blunt hull damage weaponry, and reinforcements. Get ready!</text>
			<environment type="asteroid"/>
			<ship load="SHIP_RK_BAM_EXIT_BOSS" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Fight the Punk Gatekeeper!</text>
		<event>
			<text>You think your best shot is against the Punk, with their sneaky high-tech weaponry and crew shenanigans. Get ready!</text>
			<environment type="pulsar"/>
			<ship load="SHIP_RK_PUNK_EXIT_BOSS" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Fight the Scorch Gatekeeper!</text>
		<event>
			<text>You think your best shot is against the Scorch, with their fire weaponry and acceleration features. Get ready!</text>
			<environment type="sun"/>
			<ship load="SHIP_RK_SCORCH_EXIT_BOSS" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	
	<choice hidden="true" req="unique_alkali">
		<text>(Alkali) Have Alkali clear you for leaving.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Fortunately, it only takes a few minutes before Alkali returns, and you're allowed to leave. Guess it pays to have a genius scientist secretly working with the RK Punk aboard your ship.</text>
			<autoReward level="LOW">standard</autoReward>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="unique_ariadne">
		<text>(Ariadne) Have Ariadne clear you for leaving.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Fortunately, it only takes a few minutes before Ariadne returns, and you're allowed to leave. Guess it pays to have a respected admiral in deep business with the RK Scorch aboard your ship.</text>
			<autoReward level="LOW">standard</autoReward>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_VARIANT_BILLY">
		<text>(Billy) Have Billy clear you for leaving.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Fortunately, it only takes a few minutes before Billy returns, and you're allowed to leave. Guess it pays to have the CEO of a military tech corporation aboard your ship.</text>
			<autoReward level="LOW">standard</autoReward>
			<!-- <weapon name="HEKTAR_MODULAR_WEAPONS"/> -->
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="unique_dessius">
		<text>(Dessius) Have Dessius clear you for leaving.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Fortunately, it only takes a few minutes before Dessius returns, and you're allowed to leave. Guess it pays to have an ancestral leader trading a lot of manpower to the RK aboard your ship.</text>
			<autoReward level="LOW">standard</autoReward>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="unique_devorak">
		<text>(Devorak) Have Devorak clear you for leaving.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Fortunately, it only takes a few minutes before Devorak returns, and you're allowed to leave. Guess it pays to have a warrior with an endless record of explosions studied by the RK Bam aboard your ship.</text>
			<autoReward level="LOW">standard</autoReward>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="traitor">
		<text>(Metyunt) Have Metyunt clear you for leaving.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Fortunately, it only takes a few minutes before Metyunt returns, and you're allowed to leave. Guess it pays to have the staff manager of a military tech corporation aboard your ship.</text>
			<autoReward level="LOW">standard</autoReward>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

